abstract: United States congressional delegation concludes visit to Cuba optimistic about trade deal with country, despite fact that it missed meeting with Pres Raul Castro; delegation, which included Sens Patrick Leahy, Debbie Stabenow and Richard Durbin, met with dissidents, which Cuban officials objected to and which may have led to Castro skipping meeting.
lead_paragraph: An expected session with President Raúl Castro did not materialize after the delegation met with several Cuba dissidents.
snippet: An expected session with President Raúl Castro did not materialize after the delegation met with several Cuba dissidents.

headline.main: Members of Congress, in Cuba, Discuss Trade but Don’t Meet With Castro
headline.print_headline: Members of Congress, in Cuba, Discuss Trade but Don’t Meet With Castro
